11/02/2010
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Justice Minister Barisa Colak and Croatian counterpart Ivan Simonovic signed an agreement Wednesday (February 10th) that prevents convicted criminals with dual citizenship to avoid prison by fleeing to their second homeland. It takes effect immediately. More than 100 people convicted in BiH are currently in Croatia, while 50 Croatian convicts have similarly fled to BiH. (RTRS, Srna, BHRT, AP, DPA, Reuters - 10/02/10)
